            <trans-unit id="overview.text">
                <source>overview.text</source>
                <target><![CDATA[
                               <p>
                                          This Help section covers only the basic core functionality of the cms including Pages, Menus, Media and Users.
                              </p>

                              <p><h2>Terms</h2></p>
                              <p><table id="table24404" class=""><tbody><tr><td>Page</td><td>holds content<br></td></tr><tr><td>URL<br></td><td>a string that reflects a page (e.g. "/company/employees")<br></td></tr><tr><td>Menu item<br></td><td>a single link in a menu with its name and URL<br></td></tr><tr><td>Menu<br></td><td>a set of menu items<br></td></tr><tr><td>Media<br></td><td>media files used in the content (e.g. Images, Videos)<br></td></tr><tr><td>User<br></td><td>a person with a login to your website</td></tr></tbody></table></p>

                              <p><h2>The Glue</h2></p>
                              <p>Pages hold a set of contents. A page is always accessible through its unique URL. Pages are independent from Menus.
                                          <br>
                                          <br>A menu item has a name and links to a Page or to a custom URL.
                                      </p>

                              <p><h2>Basic Workflow</h2></p>
                              <p>
                                          1. Add a new Page
                                          <br />2. Edit the new Page
                                          <br />3. Create a Menu item and link to the new Page &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p> ]]>

