            </trans-unit>
            <trans-unit id="networking_init_cms.page.admin.page.create.text">
                <source>networking_init_cms.page.admin.page.create.text</source>
                <target><![CDATA[    <p>All fields, marked with * are mandatory. But we recommend to fill out all the fields. Every input can be changed later.</p>

                           <h2>Overview of the fields</h2>

                           <p><strong>Language</strong>&nbsp;Each Page can only belong to one Language. Language Copy for this Page can be made in the next step of the process</p>

                           <p><strong>Page Name&nbsp;</strong>Just for internal use, not shown in the frontend</p>

                           <p><strong>Parent Page</strong>&nbsp;if another page is related to this one (e.g. About Us =&gt; Contact), the pages can be connected. This will be shown in the list view of the Pages as well in the URL: e.g. http://wwww.site.com/about_us/contact instead of&nbsp;http://wwww.site.com/contact</p>

                           <p><strong>URL&nbsp;</strong>only the last part of the URL has to be entered. If there is one ore more parent Pages, they will be automaticly enterd to the URL. No Special Characters can be used in an URL. Those will be automaticly filterd out. Above the input field, the Preview URL is always shown.</p>

                           <p><strong>Visibility&nbsp;</strong>a page can be either public and be seen by everyone, or it is protected by a passwort.</p>

                           <p><strong>Page Layout&nbsp;</strong>choose the layout, that fits your page the best</p>

                           <p><strong>Meta Title</strong>&nbsp;This Title is shown it the Browser Title</p>

                           <p><strong>Meta Keywords&nbsp;</strong>Keywords are not shown on the page, but only in the source code of the page. Those are needet by google and other search engines to index your page</p>

                           <p><strong>Meta Description&nbsp;</strong>As the keywords above, descrition is only visible in the source code. It&#39;s also used by search engines.</p>

                           <p>As soon the &quot;create&quot; button is clicked, the page is saved to the database and the &quot;<a class="link-underlined" href="/admin/help/networking_init_cms.page.admin.page/edit">edit page</a>&quot; is shown.</p>
                             ]]></target>
            </trans-unit>

