            <trans-unit id="networking_init_cms.menu.admin.menu_item.navigation.text">
                <source>networking_init_cms.menu.admin.menu_item.navigation.text</source>
                <target><![CDATA[ <p>
                                       A websites can have multiple menus, for example a "Main" Menu and a "secondary" Menu.
                                       <br>
                                       <br>A Menu usually has several menu items.

                                   </p>


                           <p><h2>Menu Language</h2></p>
                           <p>
                                       A Menu belongs to the selected Language only.
                                       <br>Thus every Language has it's own menus.
                                   </p>

                           <p><h2>Menu Item</h2></p>
                           <p>
                                       A menu item consists of a name and corresponding link (URL).
                                       <br>Menu items can be organized hierarchically. In other words, a menu item can have a parent menu item.
                                   </p>

                           <p><h2>Menu Item Name</h2></p>
                           <p>
                                       The Name of a menu item can be any string of your choice.
                                       <br>If you like you can use the same term as for the Page Name it links to, but you can also name it anything else.
                           </p>

                           <p><h2>Menu Item Link</h2></p>
                           <p>A menu item links to a Page or to a custom URL.
                                       <br>Different menu items can link to the same Page. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;</p><p></p>  ]]></target>
            </trans-unit>


